18ï¸âƒ£ Very Short Exam Answer (4â€“5 lines)

Proxy Pattern is a structural design pattern where a proxy object controls access to a real object. It is used for lazy loading, access control, caching, and security. The proxy and real object share the same interface. It improves performance and system security.

